Simulate tracks

simul_trks.Rd

This function simulates tracks inside a specified polygon.

Usage

simul_trks(
  anims,
  study_site,
  theta,
  vmin,
  vmax,
  rel_site,
  crs,
  n_days,
  initHeading
)

Arguments

anims

integer. quantity of desired animals to simulate

study_site

simple feature polygon object that encompasses area where tracks are allowed to be simulated.

theta

argument from glatos::crw_in_polygon function

vmin

numeric. minimum velocity from which to sample step length

vmax

numeric. maximum velocity from which to sample step length

rel_site

simple feature polygon object in which simulated animals are "released" or where simulated tracks begin

crs

EPSG code for study_site polygon. Must be projected coordinate system

n_days

integer. number of days that tracks should be simulated

initHeading

argument from glatos::crw_in_polygon function

Value

simple feature (multi)linestring object that represents individual simulated tracks

Examples

library(sporeg)
library(sf)
library(glatos)
#> version 0.8.0 ('very-refreshing-lemonade')

load(system.file("extdata", "fo_rel_site.Rda", package = "sporeg"))
load(system.file("extdata", "fo_study_site.Rda", package = "sporeg"))

anims <- 30
study_site <- fo_study_site
yr <- 1
theta <- c(0, 1.74)
vmin <- 0.98
vmax <- 1.58
rel_site <- fo_rel_site
crs <- 3857
n_days <- 365*yr
initHeading <- 0

tracks <- simul_trks(anims, study_site, theta, vmin, vmax, rel_site, crs, n_days, initHeading)
